President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Idaho due to straight-line winds that occurred on January 13, 2021. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Thomas J. Dargan has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Further information can be obtained by contacting the FEMA News Desk.